replies.bodyText:
This is due to a conflict between the Eclipse compiler and the MVN command line compiler. The outer class is marked @NonNullByDefault so by definition the inner class inherits this annotation, and therefore @NonNullByDefault is not necessary explicitly on the inner class. However MVN raises an error that @NonNullByDefault must be applied. Whereas Eclipse raises an error that @NonNullByDefault must not be applied. And so I apply @SuppressWarnings("null") to make them both happy :)
